{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"cling wrap, parchment paper, pastry brush, baking sheet, rolling pin, silicone mat, refrigerator, oven","id":"r238851","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-xl1AFdnHs6A\/XZWr5T8NBXI\/AAAAAAAAfuo\/LnehYVriP0wt1t44ikEEF2Ovil6V3hbzwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_yRLbUlUndMKe9wi5.png","title":"Mixed Berry Hand Pies","publishedAt":"2017-08-18T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Dough"},{"content":"14 oz all-purpose flour"},{"content":"8 oz unsalted butter, chilled, cubed (½ in.)"},{"content":"1 pinch salt"},{"content":"2 oz ice water"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"4 oz strawberries, hulled"},{"content":"4 oz blackberries"},{"content":"2 oz sugar"},{"content":"1 tsp lemon juice"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"whole milk, to brush"},{"content":"turbinado sugar, to sprinkle"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"21 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"42 g","calories":"1569 kJ \/ 375 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Dough"},{"content":"Place flour, butter and salt into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Add water and mix <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer dough to a clean surface. Without overworking the dough, quickly pat together and form into a flattened square. Divide in half, wrap each half in cling wrap and refrigerate 30 minutes. Meanwhile make berry filling."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"Place strawberries, blackberries, sugar and lemon juice into mixing bowl, place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid and cook <b>28 min\/212°F\/speed 0.5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate until needed."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Line a baking sheet with parchment and set aside."},{"content":"Working with one dough packet at a time, roll into a rectangle (approx. 10 in. x 13 in. x ⅛ in.) directly on a silicone mat. Refrigerate first sheet while working with remaining dough. Cut ½ inch off each side to even out dough and cut each piece into 9 rectangles (approx. 3 in. x 4 in.), (see Tip)."},{"content":"Lightly brush edges of the dough with milk. Place a heaping tablespoon of reserved berry filling in the center of each rectangle. Cover with remaining 9 dough pieces and seal edges with the tines of a fork. Place on prepared baking sheet and refrigerate 30 minutes."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 350°F."},{"content":"Prick the top of each hand pie multiple times with a fork to create steam vents. Brush tops with milk and sprinkle with turbinado sugar. Bake for 25-30 minutes (350°F) until pastry is golden brown. Let cool completely before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If dough becomes too soft, place in freezer for 10-15 minutes for easier handling.","Make on the weekend and freeze for lunches and treats.","Rolling dough directly on silicone mats will make it easier to chill soft dough and\/or freeze hand pies for baking later. Alternately, roll dough between two sheets of cling wrap.","Any berry can be used for this recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 50m","9 pieces"]}